# C# conventions (TaskManagerWpf)

## Naming
- Public types/members: `PascalCase`
- Private fields: `_camelCase`
- Async methods: suffix `Async`
- Use explicit names for booleans: `isNew`, `hasErrors`, `canAct...`

## Nullability
- Respect `Nullable=enable`.
- Prefer `string?` for optional text; normalize “empty” to `null` where it simplifies UX.

## Collections & LINQ
- Avoid LINQ in hot UI paths; use it for readability in non-critical code.
- When saving, prefer cloning/snapshots over saving VM instances.

## Error handling
- Never `catch {}` unless the intent is explicit and safe.
- If an operation fails (load/save), show a meaningful message via `IMessageService`.

## Testing hooks
- If your code depends on WPF `CollectionView`, tests may need STA (`StaTest.Run`).
